	            email="pcarbo@uchicago.edu"))
Title: Smoothing using Adaptive Shrinkage in R
Version: 1.1-7
Date: 2018-05-20
Description: Fast, wavelet-based Empirical Bayes shrinkage methods for
    signal denoising, including smoothing Poisson-distributed data and
    Gaussian-distributed data with possibly heteroskedastic error. The
    algorithms implement the methods described in "Smoothing via adaptive
    shrinkage (smash): denoising Poisson and heteroskedastic Gaussian
    signals" (Z. Xing & M. Stephens, 2016, <arXiv:1605.07787>).
